This paper discusses the impact of subsidization on the Internet and its potential as a model for the future. The paper focuses on the network and information theory aspects of the Internet, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.NI sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses competition among content providers, which could fall under the cs.IT sub-category. The paper also discusses the regulation of access prices, which could fall under the cs.CC sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential harm to certain content providers, which could fall under the cs.CR sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the welfare of the Internet content market, which could fall under the cs.GT sub-category.
